<map version='1.0.1'><node TEXT='Understanding DHCP and Its Functionality' CREATED='1729972798812' ID='ID_root' MODIFIED='1729972798812'><image/><imageSize/><icon/><node TEXT='Overview' CREATED='1729972798812' ID='ID_m2ql4yn03adma7urs85' MODIFIED='1729972798812' POSITION='right'><image/><imageSize/><icon/></node><node TEXT='What is DHCP?' CREATED='1729972798812' ID='ID_m2ql4yn0ytc22won4lh' MODIFIED='1729972798812' POSITION='right'><image/><imageSize/><icon/></node><node TEXT='Components of DHCP' CREATED='1729972798812' ID='ID_m2ql4yn0b7fruqp24pp' MODIFIED='1729972798812' POSITION='right'><image/><imageSize/><icon/><node TEXT='1. DHCP Server: A server or router that stores network configuration information.' CREATED='1729972798812' ID='ID_m2ql4yn0v3cqcgin45j' MODIFIED='1729972798812'><image/><imageSize/><icon/></node><node TEXT='2. DHCP Client: The device (e.g., computer, mobile) that receives configuration info from the server.' CREATED='1729972798812' ID='ID_m2ql4yn08cpsj2c0h79' MODIFIED='1729972798812'><image/><imageSize/><icon/></node><node TEXT='3. DHCP Relay Agent: For networks with multiple LANs, this forwards DHCP requests to the server.' CREATED='1729972798812' ID='ID_m2ql4yn0hlttt19gl7j' MODIFIED='1729972798812'><image/><imageSize/><icon/></node><node TEXT='4. IP Address Pool: A list of available IP addresses for assignment to clients.' CREATED='1729972798812' ID='ID_m2ql4yn0hvcm8xyhy5m' MODIFIED='1729972798812'><image/><imageSize/><icon/></node><node TEXT='5. Subnet Mask: Indicates the network to which the host belongs.' CREATED='1729972798812' ID='ID_m2ql4yn0zy31ljhujn' MODIFIED='1729972798812'><image/><imageSize/><icon/></node><node TEXT='6. Lease Time: Duration for which the IP address is available to the client; it must be renewed after this time.' CREATED='1729972798812' ID='ID_m2ql4yn01rtcl8nv4ff' MODIFIED='1729972798812'><image/><imageSize/><icon/></node><node TEXT='7. Gateway Address: Informs the host where to connect to the internet.' CREATED='1729972798812' ID='ID_m2ql4yn0pdtqf5vsb0i' MODIFIED='1729972798812'><image/><imageSize/><icon/></node></node><node TEXT='How Does DHCP Work?' CREATED='1729972798812' ID='ID_m2ql4yn03h477mxdjm9' MODIFIED='1729972798812' POSITION='left'><image/><imageSize/><icon/><node TEXT='DHCP Discovery: The DHCP client broadcasts messages to find DHCP servers.' CREATED='1729972798812' ID='ID_m2ql4yn01zxq14zycsa' MODIFIED='1729972798812'><image/><imageSize/><icon/><node TEXT='It sends a packet to the broadcast address (255.255.255.255) or a specific subnet address.' CREATED='1729972798812' ID='ID_m2ql4yn0ntlmjxuj7ck' MODIFIED='1729972798812'><image/><imageSize/><icon/></node></node><node TEXT='DHCP Offer: Upon receiving a Discovery message, the DHCP server sends an Offer message with a proposed IP address and other details such as subnet mask and default gateway.' CREATED='1729972798812' ID='ID_m2ql4yn0jnwwncwttx8' MODIFIED='1729972798812'><image/><imageSize/><icon/></node><node TEXT='DHCP Request: The client may receive multiple offers but will choose one and send a Request to that server, rejecting other offers.' CREATED='1729972798812' ID='ID_m2ql4yn0aul7tma5ex9' MODIFIED='1729972798812'><image/><imageSize/><icon/></node><node TEXT='DHCP Acknowledgment: The server sends an Acknowledgment to confirm the lease of the IP address, completing the IP configuration.' CREATED='1729972798812' ID='ID_m2ql4yn0e5z365y71u' MODIFIED='1729972798812'><image/><imageSize/><icon/></node></node><node TEXT='Advantages of DHCP' CREATED='1729972798812' ID='ID_m2ql4yn0jszgipaixpr' MODIFIED='1729972798812' POSITION='left'><image/><imageSize/><icon/><node TEXT='1. Easy implementation with automatic IP address assignment ensures accuracy.' CREATED='1729972798812' ID='ID_m2ql4yn0hk5nhu8uxnh' MODIFIED='1729972798812'><image/><imageSize/><icon/></node><node TEXT='2. No manual configuration is needed, saving time for network administrators.' CREATED='1729972798812' ID='ID_m2ql4yn0a7uiqtx22ir' MODIFIED='1729972798812'><image/><imageSize/><icon/></node><node TEXT='3. Eliminates duplicate or invalid IP assignments, preventing conflicts.' CREATED='1729972798812' ID='ID_m2ql4yn08nuluj21i3d' MODIFIED='1729972798812'><image/><imageSize/><icon/></node><node TEXT='4. Mobile users benefit as they automatically acquire new configurations when changing networks.' CREATED='1729972798812' ID='ID_m2ql4yn00r51yjsz3y7c' MODIFIED='1729972798812'><image/><imageSize/><icon/></node></node><node TEXT='Disadvantages of DHCP' CREATED='1729972798812' ID='ID_m2ql4yn0vq6lxjuq1o' MODIFIED='1729972798812' POSITION='left'><image/><imageSize/><icon/><node TEXT='1. Lack of secure client authentication can lead to unauthorized access and IP address depletion.' CREATED='1729972798812' ID='ID_m2ql4yn0jsjwpblom3l' MODIFIED='1729972798812'><image/><imageSize/><icon/></node><node TEXT='2. A single DHCP server poses a risk of being a single point of failure in a network.' CREATED='1729972798812' ID='ID_m2ql4yn0dn7busz41zu' MODIFIED='1729972798812'><image/><imageSize/><icon/></node></node></node></map>